## P1 findings

### P1: CI can mask failures in the federation second-implementation gate

Evidence: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` lines 18-22 pipe the Go replay and Python differential through `tail -1`:

```yaml
./impl-go/sigma-federation-go replay tests/spec_conformance/federation_vectors.json | tail -1
python3 tests/federation_differential.py | tail -1
```

GitHub Actions' default shell for `run:` blocks does not enable `pipefail`. I verified the masking behavior locally:

```bash
bash -c 'false | tail -1'; echo "exit=$?"
# exit=0
```

So a failing Go replay or differential command can be hidden if `tail` exits successfully. This is specifically dangerous here because the release's Book III claim depends on the second implementation and differential agreement.

Concrete fix proposal:

```yaml
- name: Federation second implementation (Go) + differential
  shell: bash
  run: |
    set -euo pipefail
    cd impl-go && go build -o sigma-federation-go . && cd ..
    ./impl-go/sigma-federation-go replay tests/spec_conformance/federation_vectors.json \
      | tee /dev/stderr | grep -q "FEDERATION-GO: ALL PASS"
    python3 tests/federation_differential.py \
      | tee /dev/stderr | grep -q "FEDERATION-DIFFERENTIAL: ALL AGREE"
```

